nodes.text: Terazods were large, friendly, semiaquatic mammals native to the Gungan swamps of Naboo. They grazed along swamp bottoms and slept upon moist sandbanks.

The terazod, the falumpaset, and the fambaa represented three different within the Gungan Swamps: they were three plant-eaters that existed in the same territory but had different feeding strategies. In the case of the terazod, it floated and snorkeled when feeding on underwater plant life.
